The paper discusses the communication and signal processing techniques for radiative wireless power transfer (WPT), which involves the transmission of power wirelessly. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.IT (Information Theory), which deals with the transmission and processing of information. 

The paper also discusses the electromagnetic (EM) aspects of WPT, such as energy beamforming and safety issues, which suggests the category cs.EM (Electromagnetics). 

The paper also discusses system-level design and control, which suggests the category cs.SY (Systems and Control). 

The paper briefly mentions the use of millimeter wave (mmWave) technology, which suggests the category cs.MM (Multimedia). 

Finally, the paper discusses the co-design of wireless power and communication systems, which suggests the category cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture).
